14:13.253 --> 14:14.955
It's not like that.

14:14.988 --> 14:16.957
Besides, I'm not
gonna confide in a man

14:16.990 --> 14:18.558
whose most
meaningful relationship

14:18.591 --> 14:19.893
is with his surfboard.

14:19.927 --> 14:23.630
[ Chuckles ]
And whose fault is that?

14:23.663 --> 14:25.265
Are you jealous?

14:25.298 --> 14:26.499
[ Laughs ]

14:26.533 --> 14:27.434
Check it out.

14:27.467 --> 14:29.869
Here he goes.

14:32.405 --> 14:34.274
[ Car alarm chirps ]

14:37.677 --> 14:39.546
[ Engine starts ]

14:48.055 --> 14:51.925
[ Rock music plays ]

14:53.093 --> 14:54.261
[ Gunshots ]

14:54.294 --> 14:55.595
[ Woman screams ]

14:55.628 --> 14:57.130
You see this?

14:57.164 --> 14:59.332
That's Mrs. Millstone
in the background.

14:59.366 --> 15:01.301
If you want me to feel
sorry for her, I don't.

15:01.334 --> 15:03.203
She's still wearing
her wedding band.

15:03.236 --> 15:05.438
That has to be
20k worth of diamonds.

15:05.472 --> 15:06.573
Pretty hard to miss.

15:06.606 --> 15:08.175
Why wouldn't
they take her ring?

15:08.208 --> 15:10.010
They got plenty.

15:10.043 --> 15:12.946
Maybe. Only how'd they know
about the safe?

15:12.980 --> 15:14.481
Let me ask you
a question.

15:14.514 --> 15:15.949
[ Gunshot ]

15:15.983 --> 15:18.285
What did Lockhart want?

15:18.318 --> 15:20.353
She told me about
you and Millstone.

15:20.387 --> 15:22.555
About Robin Meyers,
the witness who disappeared.

15:22.589 --> 15:25.292
Disappeared my ass.

15:25.325 --> 15:27.694
Robin Meyers was murdered.

15:27.727 --> 15:29.196
[ Gunshot ]

15:30.263 --> 15:32.565
She didn't want to testify.

15:32.599 --> 15:36.403
I was the one who promised her
things would be okay.

15:41.474 --> 15:45.312
So, I have to get up on
the stand and say what I saw?

15:45.345 --> 15:46.613
That's right.

15:46.646 --> 15:48.315
And McQueen will be there?

15:48.348 --> 15:51.651
He will, but I'll be in
the courtroom with you, too.

15:51.684 --> 15:52.752
I'm scared.

15:52.785 --> 15:54.387
I know. I would be, too.

15:54.421 --> 15:56.623
But you're the only one
who can put him away.

15:59.559 --> 16:02.362
You promise me
I'll be okay?

16:02.395 --> 16:03.997
I promise.

16:04.031 --> 16:07.000
So you think Millstone had
something to do with it?

16:07.034 --> 16:10.737
A few years after Robin,
a witness, not one of mine,

16:10.770 --> 16:12.672
went missing on another
Millstone case.

16:12.705 --> 16:14.207
Three more since.

16:14.241 --> 16:15.508
How do you know it's not
Millstone's clients

16:15.542 --> 16:16.743
who took out the witnesses?

16:16.776 --> 16:18.411
Look at the evidence.
What evidence?

16:18.445 --> 16:19.612
Exactly.
There isn't any.

16:19.646 --> 16:21.614
No prints,
no casings, nothing.

16:21.648 --> 16:24.417
It's too clean.
His clients aren't that smart.

16:24.451 --> 16:27.154
Millstone's behind this.
I know it.

16:27.187 --> 16:29.356
Lockhart's waiting for you
to make a mistake, Frank.

16:29.389 --> 16:31.124
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
And she thinks because

16:31.158 --> 16:32.992
this is personal for you,
you'll get sloppy.

16:36.296 --> 16:39.499
I got to pick up Holly
for this ambush

16:39.532 --> 16:40.767
your wife planned for us.

16:40.800 --> 16:42.435
Nothing I could do.

16:42.469 --> 16:44.704
Well, just make sure
she doesn't serve dessert.

16:44.737 --> 16:46.673
I want to make it
an early evening.

16:46.706 --> 16:48.575
Hey.

16:50.343 --> 16:52.512
How'd you know the crew
wouldn't show that night

16:52.545 --> 16:54.547
during the stakeout?

16:56.083 --> 16:59.219
I've been doing this
a long time, trainee.

16:59.686 --> 17:01.454
Maybe too long.

17:06.759 --> 17:09.296
[ Elevator door slams ]

17:18.571 --> 17:21.608
I see you went with
the chicken-fried steak.

17:21.641 --> 17:22.809
Brave men.

17:22.842 --> 17:24.811
[ Clears throat ]

17:24.844 --> 17:27.314
Have something for me?

17:32.485 --> 17:34.354
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
I look like a pawn shop?

17:34.387 --> 17:35.722
That's for you, stupid.

17:35.755 --> 17:37.324
What's for me?

17:42.729 --> 17:45.432
Files and a phone.

17:45.465 --> 17:47.534
Okay, now we're talking.

17:50.270 --> 17:51.571
What, do you got
to make wee wee?

17:51.604 --> 17:53.340
The hell you so nervous about?

17:53.373 --> 17:55.308
If anybody sees us talking to
you, they'll think we snitches.

17:55.342 --> 17:57.344
Looks bad breaking bread
with a cop.

17:57.377 --> 17:59.779
Kyle:
I couldn't agree more.

18:02.415 --> 18:04.484
[ Chuckles ]
You followed me?

18:04.517 --> 18:06.119
Okay, I'm impressed.

18:06.153 --> 18:07.187
A little.

18:07.220 --> 18:08.255
Who the hell is this?

18:08.288 --> 18:09.356
Oh, you want
to be introduced?

18:09.389 --> 18:13.126
Lou, Danny...
meet Kyle Craig.

18:13.160 --> 18:16.363
Kyle, meet our home invaders.

18:23.603 --> 18:25.305
You finally lost in, Frank.

18:25.338 --> 18:26.739
I knew something was off!

18:26.773 --> 18:28.908
I couldn't figure out
how you were so sure

18:28.941 --> 18:30.443
the crew wouldn't hit again.

18:30.477 --> 18:32.279
But hiring those fools
to jack Millstone,

18:32.312 --> 18:33.613
I will not go along with this.

18:33.646 --> 18:35.148
Just hear me out.

18:35.182 --> 18:36.783
I got a tip on those
Beverly Hills break-ins

18:36.816 --> 18:38.918
Val briefed us about
and gaffled Lou and Danny.

18:38.951 --> 18:40.387
We cut a deal.

18:40.420 --> 18:41.754
They hit Millstone's,
keep the loot,

18:41.788 --> 18:43.790
and I get the contents
of Millstone's safe.

18:43.823 --> 18:47.327
Only the District Attorney
is authorized to make deals.

18:47.360 --> 18:48.828
Look at this.
So what?

18:48.861 --> 18:50.863
It's locked. I got to see
if Rebecca can hack it.

18:50.897 --> 18:52.532
So you're gonna rope her
into this?

18:52.565 --> 18:54.867
Millstone's been having
witnesses killed, Kyle.

18:54.901 --> 18:56.469
He's been getting away
with it for years,

18:56.503 --> 18:57.904
and he's gonna keep on
getting away with it.

18:57.937 --> 18:59.539
I think I finally found
a way to prove it.

18:59.572 --> 19:03.876
I'm not gonna go to prison
chasing one of your hunches.

19:03.910 --> 19:07.480
We're gonna be
late for dinner.

19:07.514 --> 19:10.483
[ Laughter ]

19:10.517 --> 19:12.452
So, I'm a boot
fresh out of the academy.

19:12.485 --> 19:14.587
I don't know my ass
from my elbow,

19:14.621 --> 19:16.823
and I open it,
cats come pouring out.

19:16.856 --> 19:18.358
I mean, dozens of cats.

19:18.391 --> 19:20.527
There's more cats every time
he tells this story.

19:20.560 --> 19:22.229
Well, trust me,
a lot of cats.

19:22.262 --> 19:24.231
So, what'd you do?
Only thing I could do.

19:24.264 --> 19:26.566
I stood up on a chair,
put one hand over my privates.

19:26.599 --> 19:28.335
I hold up my lighter
to the ceiling

19:28.368 --> 19:29.802
and trigger
the sprinkler system.

19:29.836 --> 19:31.371
The water comes
spraying out,

19:31.404 --> 19:33.340
and these cats, man,
they just scattered.

19:33.373 --> 19:34.907
Is he this funny
all the time?

19:34.941 --> 19:37.677
-[ Chuckles ]
-Nope.

19:37.710 --> 19:40.980
[ Chuckles ]

19:41.013 --> 19:43.650
Well, we don't want
to overstay our welcome.

19:43.683 --> 19:45.552
Alyse, you probably
have an early shift.

19:45.585 --> 19:46.786
Oh, no, it's fine.

19:46.819 --> 19:48.921
I'm actually off
tonight and tomorrow.

19:48.955 --> 19:50.523
What are you gonna do
with your day?

19:50.557 --> 19:51.924
I thought about
taking a yoga class.

19:51.958 --> 19:53.593
You know,
we should go together.

19:53.626 --> 19:56.263
I take an 11:00 A.M.
in Larchmont three days a week.

19:56.296 --> 19:58.365
Amazing. I'd be lucky
if I make one class a week.

19:58.398 --> 19:59.932
Your schedule must be
pretty flexible.

19:59.966 --> 20:01.801
Are you self-employed?

20:01.834 --> 20:03.436
I am.

20:03.470 --> 20:06.673
I run my own business,
so I make my own hours.

20:06.706 --> 20:09.809
Really?
What kind of business?

20:09.842 --> 20:12.312
I run a dating service.

20:12.345 --> 20:14.714
Like an online thing?

20:14.747 --> 20:18.251
It's more of
an escort service.

20:19.719 --> 20:20.953
Escort service.

20:20.987 --> 20:22.755
Oh, okay.

20:22.789 --> 20:25.292
So, is that
how you two met?

20:25.325 --> 20:26.626
-No, not really.
-Yep.

20:26.659 --> 20:27.860
[ Both laugh ]

20:27.894 --> 20:29.829
On second thought,
I think we really do

20:29.862 --> 20:31.698
have to wake up
early tomorrow.

20:31.731 --> 20:34.767
We don't, sweetie. Frank,
can I get you another beer?

20:39.539 --> 20:40.707
Sure.

20:40.740 --> 20:44.043
[ Cellphone rings ]

20:44.076 --> 20:45.945
Oh.
This is the hospital.

20:45.978 --> 20:47.880
Excuse me one second.

20:47.914 --> 20:49.716
[ Sighs ]
I'm gonna use the head.

20:49.749 --> 20:51.951
Oh, Frank.

20:52.652 --> 20:54.754
[ Sighs ]

20:54.787 --> 20:56.489
[ Door opens ]

20:56.523 --> 20:58.291
[ Door closes ]

20:58.325 --> 21:01.361
You know, we've got
something in common.

21:01.394 --> 21:05.565
We both know it's not easy
having Frank for a partner.

21:05.598 --> 21:08.601
Tell me about it.

21:08.635 --> 21:10.637
Riding with you
is good for Frank.

21:10.670 --> 21:12.339
He'd kill me for
telling you this,

21:12.372 --> 21:14.006
but when you were gonna
be his trainee,

21:14.040 --> 21:16.876
it was the happiest
I'd seen him in a long time.

21:16.909 --> 21:19.011
Frank and your dad
were like brothers.

21:19.045 --> 21:23.883
Frank never fully recovered
after losing Billy.

21:23.916 --> 21:25.452
[ Chuckles ]

21:25.485 --> 21:29.922
I know this is
a lot to ask, Kyle.

21:29.956 --> 21:34.494
I know who Frank is,
how he can be.

21:34.527 --> 21:41.100
Please just watch out for him
the way your dad did.

21:41.133 --> 21:43.035
He needs you.

21:51.678 --> 21:53.646
You invited Frank
to a dinner party?

21:53.680 --> 21:54.881
It was my wife's idea.

21:54.914 --> 21:56.449
She wanted to meet
my training officer.

21:56.483 --> 21:57.584
Where's Tommy?

21:57.617 --> 21:58.951
[ Sighs ]
Still watching Parker.

21:58.985 --> 22:01.388
Frank asked me to look into
Millstone's phone.

22:01.421 --> 22:02.422
You knew, didn't you?

22:02.455 --> 22:03.823
About the home invasion?

22:03.856 --> 22:06.393
Not until last night.

22:06.426 --> 22:07.727
I don't question Frank.

22:07.760 --> 22:10.530
Frank hunts the things
that hunt the innocent.

22:10.563 --> 22:12.799
If he played by the rules,
I probably would've died

22:12.832 --> 22:15.535
somebody's plaything, my organs
sold off on the black market.

22:15.568 --> 22:17.937
So if it's a choice between
rules and results, guess what.

22:17.970 --> 22:20.540
[ Elevator door slams ]

22:20.573 --> 22:23.543
So, good times at
the Craig house last night.

22:23.576 --> 22:24.711
A few thoughts, trainee.

22:24.744 --> 22:26.579
Sort of a post mortem.

22:26.613 --> 22:29.916
One -- under no circumstances
are we ever doing that again.

22:29.949 --> 22:33.085
Your wife's a good cook, but our
women should never hang out.

22:33.119 --> 22:35.555
Too many trade secrets
for the both of us.

22:35.588 --> 22:36.723
Anything else?

22:36.756 --> 22:38.157
Yeah.
Buy some domestic beer.

22:38.190 --> 22:40.660
You don't deserve Holly.
You know that, right?

22:42.995 --> 22:45.498
Were you able
to crack the phone?

22:45.532 --> 22:48.134
Millstone was using an advanced
symmetric block cypher.

22:48.167 --> 22:51.838
Basically an algorithm that
locks down the phone's hardware.

22:51.871 --> 22:54.741
So you can't tell me
who he called?

22:54.774 --> 22:57.510
He wasn't making calls.
He was texting.

22:57.544 --> 22:58.811
Couldn't recover the texts,

22:58.845 --> 23:00.547
but I did put dates
on the transmissions.

23:00.580 --> 23:02.915
About a dozen of them
over the years.

23:02.949 --> 23:04.984
Any of it mean
anything to you?

23:05.017 --> 23:06.953
Bastard.

23:09.622 --> 23:10.623
What?

23:10.657 --> 23:11.891
June, 2010.

23:11.924 --> 23:13.059
What about it?

23:13.092 --> 23:14.794
That's when Robin Meyers
went missing.

23:14.827 --> 23:16.729
Millstone gave the order,
and whoever's on the other end

23:16.763 --> 23:18.164
of that phone
made her disappear.

23:18.197 --> 23:20.199
Frank, this last one was
just sent a few days ago.

23:20.232 --> 23:21.734
Didn't Lockhart tell you

23:21.768 --> 23:23.570
Millstone was in the middle
of a homicide trial?

23:23.603 --> 23:26.138
He's put this thing
in motion again.

23:26.172 --> 23:29.008
He's going after
another witness.

23:37.684 --> 23:40.753
-Detective Rourke.
-Ms. Finney.

23:40.787 --> 23:42.889
You need to find a place
to hide your witnesses.

23:42.922 --> 23:44.524
I beg your pardon?

23:44.557 --> 23:46.593
We have reason to believe
that one of the witnesses

23:46.626 --> 23:47.994
in your homicide trial
is at risk.

23:48.027 --> 23:50.062
I have seven witnesses,
Detective.

23:50.096 --> 23:52.865
Not including police officers,
S.I.D., or the M.E.

23:52.899 --> 23:55.067
If someone's in danger,
I need to know who it is.

23:55.101 --> 23:57.670
We can't tell you that.

23:57.704 --> 23:59.739
Detective, I thought
Chief Lockhart and I

23:59.772 --> 24:02.809
made ourselves perfectly clear
about Gary Millstone.

24:02.842 --> 24:04.811
You're in a courtroom
trying to out-lawyer him

24:04.844 --> 24:06.613
while he's out here
being an outlaw.

24:06.646 --> 24:08.214
So Millstone's the outlaw?

24:08.247 --> 24:11.117
I hope that irony
isn't lost on you, Detective.

24:12.719 --> 24:15.021
I go to the judge with
unsubstantiated allegations

24:15.054 --> 24:17.189
like this, I open myself up
to a mistrial.

24:17.223 --> 24:20.092
You don't, and one of your
witnesses can get killed.

24:21.794 --> 24:24.497
Then bring me something
I can act on.

24:24.531 --> 24:26.966
You know, something legal.

24:29.201 --> 24:32.839
[ Footsteps receding ]
Son of a bitch.

24:32.872 --> 24:34.106
[ Chuckling ] Whoa.

24:34.140 --> 24:36.108
Some nice pieces here.

24:36.142 --> 24:37.109
Special.

24:37.143 --> 24:38.177
I know, right?

24:38.210 --> 24:39.712
Like I said when I called,

24:39.746 --> 24:41.714
we deal in very selective
merchandise.

24:48.287 --> 24:50.256
[ Door opens ]
Yeah, can we just
move this along, man?

24:50.289 --> 24:53.860
Well, you two morons
clearly haven't put

24:53.893 --> 24:55.695
a lot of thought into this.

24:55.728 --> 24:59.866
Millstone represents nearly
every fence in this damn city.

24:59.899 --> 25:02.001
Thank you for your service,
Chuck.

25:02.034 --> 25:03.269
Who the hell are you?!

25:03.302 --> 25:05.137
[ Gun cocks ]

25:05.171 --> 25:08.074
I am the last guy
you want to run into

25:08.107 --> 25:12.278
while trying to fence the stuff
you stole from my employer.

25:15.848 --> 25:18.818
So...what
are we gonna do?

25:18.851 --> 25:20.019
I don't know.

25:20.052 --> 25:22.755
[ Cellphone rings ]

25:22.789 --> 25:24.757
Tommy, give me
some good news.

25:24.791 --> 25:26.525
Yeah, you're not gonna
like this, boss.

25:27.660 --> 25:33.165
Now, neither one of you
are capable of figuring out

25:33.199 --> 25:36.168
that those little paper cowboy
hats are actually meant

25:36.202 --> 25:39.171
to cover the seat
of a public toilet.

25:39.639 --> 25:44.911
Much less...put something
like this together.

25:46.946 --> 25:48.314
[ Sighs ]

25:48.347 --> 25:52.284
Somebody put you up to it.

25:59.191 --> 26:02.028
And you're gonna tell me who.

26:02.061 --> 26:04.931
[ Laughs ]

26:04.964 --> 26:08.668
You're gonna be
begging to tell me.

26:08.701 --> 26:10.102
Hmm?

26:10.803 --> 26:14.641
They call this
a Tucker Telephone.

26:18.711 --> 26:21.080
Named for
the Tucker State Prison farm

26:21.113 --> 26:25.117
back in Arkansas where
the technique was invented.

26:28.855 --> 26:33.292
Oh, it's just
an old antique hand-crank phone

26:33.325 --> 26:37.196
hardwired to a couple
of dry-cell batteries.

26:39.799 --> 26:40.833
[ Telephone ringing ]

26:40.867 --> 26:42.168
[ Both screaming ]

26:42.201 --> 26:46.706
[ Laughs ]
But man, it does the trick, huh?

26:46.739 --> 26:49.008
Who turned you on to Millstone?

26:51.711 --> 26:52.344
[ Telephone ringing ]

26:52.378 --> 26:53.780
[ Both scream ]

26:53.813 --> 26:54.847
[ Laughs ]

26:54.881 --> 26:56.115
Who has the phone?

26:56.148 --> 26:58.150
[ Screaming continues ]

27:02.722 --> 27:04.691
Tommy:
Well, that's kinky.

27:06.759 --> 27:08.861
What are you gonna do,
shoot me?

27:08.895 --> 27:10.697
I was
thinking about it.

27:13.432 --> 27:15.101
Nah.

27:16.836 --> 27:18.838
I'd rather
just kick your ass.

27:19.906 --> 27:22.574
[ Grunts ]

27:26.445 --> 27:29.716
**

27:43.896 --> 27:46.733
[ Laughs ] A genuine
Tucker Telephone.

27:46.766 --> 27:48.167
I'm geeking out here,
Parker.

27:48.200 --> 27:50.703
That's a real piece
of history.

27:50.737 --> 27:53.906
Hmm. Can you imagine what it
must've been like back then,

27:53.940 --> 27:55.775
back before
political correctness

27:55.808 --> 27:58.277
and, uh, what the hell
do you call it?

27:58.310 --> 28:00.446
Micro aggressions.

28:00.479 --> 28:02.014
[ Telephone ringing ]

28:02.048 --> 28:03.415
[ Grunts ]

28:03.449 --> 28:07.720
You know, guys like us,
today we're monsters, right?

28:07.754 --> 28:09.055
But back then,
they would've said

28:09.088 --> 28:10.289
we were too soft
on suspects.

28:10.322 --> 28:12.191
Hey.

28:12.224 --> 28:14.193
Why don't we set
the way-back machine

28:14.226 --> 28:17.063
to those thrilling days
of yesteryear?

28:17.096 --> 28:19.198
[ The Fleetwoods'
"Come Softly to Me" plays ]

28:19.231 --> 28:21.000
Eisenhower's
in the White House,

28:21.033 --> 28:24.737
and no one's ever heard of
Miranda vs. Arizona.

28:24.771 --> 28:25.772
[ Telephone ringing ]

28:25.805 --> 28:28.074
[ Grunting ]

28:29.842 --> 28:31.443
I got Millstone's
magic phone,

28:31.477 --> 28:33.746
the one that makes
witnesses disappear.

28:33.780 --> 28:35.047
Like that "Twilight Zone"

28:35.081 --> 28:36.348
where you push a button
and somebody dies.

28:36.382 --> 28:38.284
I know it's a death ray.

28:38.317 --> 28:40.219
Just don't know
how it works.

28:40.252 --> 28:42.054
Wish I could
help you out.

28:42.088 --> 28:43.489
Yeah.

28:43.522 --> 28:48.094
You know, people say that,
but they don't really mean it.

28:48.127 --> 28:49.495
I got to make
a long-distance phone call.

28:49.528 --> 28:51.097
[ Telephone ringing ]
Hello? Hello?

28:51.130 --> 28:53.432
Duluth, Duluth,
come in, come in.

28:53.465 --> 28:55.467
[ Grunting ]

28:55.501 --> 28:57.837
We found
a dozen text messages,

28:57.870 --> 28:59.972
each corresponding
to a witness who disappeared,

29:00.006 --> 29:01.507
including a nurse
named Robin Meyers.

29:01.540 --> 29:02.374
Remember her?

29:02.408 --> 29:04.076
I sure as hell do.

29:04.110 --> 29:07.046
Brave woman,
ready to testify against

29:07.079 --> 29:09.215
one of your employer's
dirt bag clients.

29:09.248 --> 29:11.217
And you guys
had her killed for it.

29:11.250 --> 29:17.089
I don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

29:17.123 --> 29:18.524
[ Telephone ringing ]
Bravo six! Bravo six!

29:18.557 --> 29:20.126
Got Charlie on the wire!
Repeat, repeat!

29:20.159 --> 29:22.461
Charlie's on the wire!
Request immediate air support!

29:22.494 --> 29:24.296
[ Screams ]

29:30.169 --> 29:32.004
Millstone used
the cellphone to text

29:32.038 --> 29:34.206
a contract killer
named Ulysses.

29:34.240 --> 29:36.408
Local, but no one knows
who he really is,

29:36.442 --> 29:37.810
not even Millstone.

29:37.844 --> 29:39.979
So Millstone can't be
tied to him.

29:40.012 --> 29:41.147
Millstone's not stupid.

29:41.180 --> 29:42.481
So how does it work?
Easy.

29:42.514 --> 29:44.383
Millstone texts a photo
of the target along with

29:44.416 --> 29:46.518
a timetable and wires money
to an offshore account,

29:46.552 --> 29:48.154
then just sits back
and waits.

29:48.187 --> 29:50.289
-A perfect system.
-Makes it impossible to prove,

29:50.322 --> 29:52.424
and a coerced confession
won't cut it.

29:52.458 --> 29:54.260
Not with me,
not with the D.A.

29:54.293 --> 29:57.529
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

29:58.597 --> 30:02.501
**

30:02.534 --> 30:04.803
[ Car alarm chirps ]

30:09.608 --> 30:11.978
Oh, you've got to be kidding me.

30:12.011 --> 30:15.281
Crying shame about the criminal
element in this city.

30:15.314 --> 30:18.184
If only lawyers like you weren't
so good at getting them off.

30:18.217 --> 30:20.052
This is low even for you,
Rourke.

30:20.086 --> 30:21.187
Man makes a good point.

30:21.220 --> 30:22.388
It's not what
you know, Gary.

30:22.421 --> 30:25.057
It's what you can prove,
remember?

30:25.091 --> 30:26.592
Like this phone.

30:26.625 --> 30:29.929
Legally, I can't say how
I came into possession of it,

30:29.962 --> 30:31.597
you understand,
and for obvious reasons,

30:31.630 --> 30:33.332
you can't tell me
it's yours either.

30:33.365 --> 30:35.401
I should've realized the other
morning you were behind this.

30:35.434 --> 30:37.203
This isn't your day, Gary.

30:37.236 --> 30:40.206
You never lost a case, but
you're about to lose two today.

30:40.239 --> 30:42.074
I don't know what
you're talking about.

30:42.108 --> 30:44.610
The one you're trying against
Regina Finney, and of course,

30:44.643 --> 30:47.346
the upcoming trial in which
you will be the star defendant.

30:47.379 --> 30:48.948
You're delusional.

30:48.981 --> 30:51.083
Multiple counts
of murder for hire,

30:51.117 --> 30:52.484
including Robin Meyers,

30:52.518 --> 30:56.355
the nurse I convinced to
testify against Cal McQueen.

30:56.388 --> 30:58.324
You had her killed
and ditched her car at LAX

30:58.357 --> 31:00.960
to make it look like
she'd run off.

31:00.993 --> 31:04.363
Nobody likes a sore loser,
Rourke.

31:04.396 --> 31:05.364
I have your phone.

31:05.397 --> 31:06.598
Phone proves nothing.

31:06.632 --> 31:07.967
You know,
that's what Parker said

31:08.000 --> 31:09.468
when he showed me
how it worked.

31:09.501 --> 31:11.103
I think I came up with
what we call a work-around

31:11.137 --> 31:13.105
that results
in your confession.

31:13.139 --> 31:15.241
You know, I'm not some
gang banger you can intimidate

31:15.274 --> 31:17.109
with your little
Marshal Dillon act, Rourke.

31:17.143 --> 31:19.245
You're not as clever
as you think you are, Gary.

31:19.278 --> 31:21.180
Actually,
it was very simple.

31:21.213 --> 31:24.116
All I had to do was
wire the money to an account

31:24.150 --> 31:26.385
in the Caymans,
the same way you did.

31:26.418 --> 31:29.989
You know, the genius of your
system is in its anonymity.

31:30.022 --> 31:31.490
Ulysses doesn't
know who you are.

31:31.523 --> 31:33.359
He just waits for
the money to hit his account,

31:33.392 --> 31:35.962
and off he goes to work.

31:35.995 --> 31:39.932
So I sent him your photo
and, uh, your Bentley's GPS.

31:39.966 --> 31:42.334
Then I thought, you know,
just to make it interesting,

31:42.368 --> 31:44.003
I'd add a little wrinkle.

31:44.036 --> 31:46.405
I texted him that I needed
the job done A.S.A.P.

31:46.438 --> 31:49.608
Figure, uh, he should
show up any minute.

31:49.641 --> 31:51.477
You have a choice,
Millstone.

31:51.510 --> 31:53.479
Use the phone and enter
the abort codes

31:53.512 --> 31:56.382
and implicate yourself.

31:56.415 --> 31:58.584
Or go ahead and die.

32:02.588 --> 32:04.656
Watch out for the red dot,
Gary.

32:04.690 --> 32:06.558
Now, you can enter
the abort code,

32:06.592 --> 32:09.295
which proves your guilt, or you
can start drafting your will.

32:09.328 --> 32:11.063
Either way,
I walk away a winner.

32:11.097 --> 32:13.132
I don't know about you,
trainee, but I think

32:13.165 --> 32:14.300
we ought to give Gary here

32:14.333 --> 32:16.102
a wide berth to consider
his options.

32:16.135 --> 32:20.506
Say, I wonder if it's
that tall guy over there.

32:23.209 --> 32:24.276
Just...

32:34.453 --> 32:38.224
Give me
the damn phone, Rourke.

32:38.257 --> 32:40.059
J-J-Just give it to me!

32:40.092 --> 32:41.160
I...

32:41.193 --> 32:42.995
I want to hear
you say it.

32:43.029 --> 32:44.330
I had her killed, okay?

32:44.363 --> 32:45.731
Robin Meyers.

32:45.764 --> 32:49.068
I paid to have her killed,
have her car left at LAX.

32:50.702 --> 32:53.139
[ Phone buttons clicking ]

33:00.246 --> 33:03.082
Standby
to trace the ping.

33:04.816 --> 33:06.718
Standing by.

33:06.752 --> 33:08.687
Copy that.

33:12.191 --> 33:14.693
[ Line ringing ]

33:16.162 --> 33:17.629
Tommy, you read me?

33:17.663 --> 33:19.398
Suspect is in the park.

33:19.431 --> 33:22.134
[ Cellphones ringing ]

33:25.671 --> 33:27.106
Who is this?

33:27.139 --> 33:28.540
Afternoon.
I was wondering if you had

33:28.574 --> 33:30.042
any interest in
home repairs.

33:30.076 --> 33:32.444
Rebecca: Lower level
near the fountain.

33:35.281 --> 33:37.549
[ Children laughing ]

33:39.518 --> 33:41.220
I have a crew
in your neighborhood

33:41.253 --> 33:43.355
who'd be happy to stop by
and talk with you.

34:06.312 --> 34:08.580
[ Gunshot ]

34:15.487 --> 34:17.489
[ People screaming ]

34:37.609 --> 34:39.545
You okay?

34:41.380 --> 34:42.648
Hey, you know
I'm the only guy

34:42.681 --> 34:44.750
who really
understands you, right?

34:44.783 --> 34:46.518
Not the time
or place, dude.

34:46.552 --> 34:48.620
[ Chuckles ] Well, we don't
really see each other

34:48.654 --> 34:49.888
outside of work,
so these are the only

34:49.921 --> 34:52.191
times and places
we do have.

35:00.632 --> 35:03.669
**

35:06.372 --> 35:08.840
Well, congratulations,
Parker.

35:08.874 --> 35:10.742
You're a douche bag
who can now add "rat"

35:10.776 --> 35:13.279
to your
online dating profile.

35:17.516 --> 35:19.285
[ Elevator dings ]

35:30.529 --> 35:32.698
Put him in
the conference room.

35:36.602 --> 35:38.904
You realize Mutt and Jeff
could tank your story, right?

35:42.541 --> 35:44.243
Lou and Danny
are long gone.

35:44.276 --> 35:47.346
Let's just say
lesson learned.

35:48.514 --> 35:50.282
So, can you really
link this maggot

35:50.316 --> 35:51.917
to the witness
in the McQueen case?

35:51.950 --> 35:55.321
Robin Meyers
and all the others.

35:55.354 --> 35:56.588
What's the matter, Joy?

35:56.622 --> 35:58.890
Not the outcome
you were expecting?

35:58.924 --> 36:03.262
I don't have expectations
when it comes to you, Frank.

36:03.295 --> 36:05.331
If you'll excuse me.

36:15.674 --> 36:17.343
[ Glass squeaking ]

36:26.985 --> 36:28.987
Come to gloat?

36:29.020 --> 36:31.557
There's nothing
to gloat about.

36:31.590 --> 36:34.926
No way to bring
those people back.

36:34.960 --> 36:36.595
But there is a way
you could bring peace

36:36.628 --> 36:38.797
to the family
of one of them.

36:40.599 --> 36:42.401
Robin Meyers.

36:42.434 --> 36:43.835
What happened to her?

36:43.869 --> 36:45.804
Why should I
tell you anything?

36:45.837 --> 36:50.409
You can survive as a lawyer
inside, but not as a snitch.

36:50.442 --> 36:53.312
You don't want McQueen
to know you ratted him out.

36:53.345 --> 36:56.382
Which is my next call.

36:56.415 --> 36:58.250
Where is she?

37:00.419 --> 37:02.521
Lake Hollywood.

37:02.554 --> 37:04.823
[ Sighs ]

37:23.542 --> 37:25.611
[ Knock on door ]

37:26.645 --> 37:29.315
Yes?

37:32.784 --> 37:35.854
Hello, Kathy.

37:35.887 --> 37:38.256
Come in.

37:46.898 --> 37:49.568
[ Door closes ]

37:49.601 --> 37:51.670
It's been a long time.

37:55.407 --> 37:57.443
We caught Robin's killer.

37:59.978 --> 38:02.781
There's also a chance
we may recover her body.

38:05.551 --> 38:07.919
At least now
you know for sure.

38:07.953 --> 38:10.021
You can let her go.

38:10.055 --> 38:12.491
Frank.

38:16.828 --> 38:19.431
You have to
let her go, too.

38:38.817 --> 38:40.586
[ Inhales deeply ]

38:46.592 --> 38:50.662
* Oh, Father, tell me

38:50.696 --> 38:55.701
* We get what we deserve

38:55.734 --> 39:03.442
* Oh, we get what we deserve

39:03.475 --> 39:07.045
* And way down we go

39:10.015 --> 39:15.053
I could get used
to this, seeing you more.

39:15.086 --> 39:17.856
* Way down we go

39:17.889 --> 39:20.859
I have to go home.

39:20.892 --> 39:23.562
I'm jealous.

39:23.595 --> 39:27.533
I can't help it.

39:27.566 --> 39:31.403
Your husband gets all of you,
and I only get what you give me.

39:31.437 --> 39:34.506
These moments.

39:34.540 --> 39:36.708
You know, it's funny.

39:36.742 --> 39:39.811
He thinks he's the only one
who really understands me.

39:39.845 --> 39:42.481
* Yeah, but for the fall

39:42.514 --> 39:46.585
But the truth is
nobody gets all of me.

39:46.618 --> 39:49.521
* Look him right
in the eyes, yeah *

39:52.491 --> 39:55.761
I'm not like your husband,
Rebecca.

39:55.794 --> 39:58.497
You knew what you were
getting yourself into.

39:58.530 --> 40:00.499
This is how
it has to be.

40:00.532 --> 40:02.801
Just tell me
if you love him.

40:04.936 --> 40:06.638
This isn't
the time or place.

40:06.672 --> 40:11.543
* We get what we deserve

40:11.577 --> 40:16.014
So, where are your unindicted
co-conspirators, Lou and Danny?

40:16.047 --> 40:18.517
On a bus
bound for Alaska.

40:18.550 --> 40:21.987
I revoked
their L.A. privileges.

40:22.020 --> 40:24.956
Don't ever put me in
this position again, Frank.

40:24.990 --> 40:27.058
This is a shotgun wedding.

40:27.092 --> 40:29.528
We're together because
we both want to find the men

40:29.561 --> 40:32.931
who murdered my dad,
and I'm willing to sacrifice

40:32.964 --> 40:36.968
everything to find them
except my principles.

40:38.970 --> 40:40.839
I won't give you those.

40:40.872 --> 40:42.741
They're mine.

40:57.656 --> 40:58.957
Hey.

40:58.990 --> 41:01.159
Look who stopped by.

41:02.928 --> 41:04.863
Ma'am.

41:07.766 --> 41:09.234
How are you?

41:11.236 --> 41:13.572
Well, I have work to do.

41:13.605 --> 41:16.074
I'll leave you guys
to it.

41:16.107 --> 41:18.476
I'll be quick, promise.

41:23.649 --> 41:25.584
She's lovely.

41:25.617 --> 41:27.252
You're a lucky man.

41:27.285 --> 41:28.620
I know.

41:28.654 --> 41:30.789
Hope you're a smart man.

41:32.223 --> 41:35.561
Look, Chief, I really don't
have anything worth reporting.

41:35.594 --> 41:36.995
Tell you what.

41:37.028 --> 41:42.601
Why don't you report something
and let me be the judge.

41:42.634 --> 41:44.603
Don't ever come
to my home again.

41:44.636 --> 41:46.104
[ Chuckles ]

41:46.137 --> 41:49.007
Boy, please.

41:49.040 --> 41:51.009
You work for me.

41:51.042 --> 41:53.511
You think this is a game?

41:55.581 --> 41:58.283
Parker was a dirty cop working
for a corrupt attorney,

41:58.316 --> 41:59.851
and you chose
to let him go

41:59.885 --> 42:01.553
because you're fixated on
catching Frank.

42:01.587 --> 42:04.790
You have no idea how much
you and Frank are alike.

42:08.927 --> 42:12.898
If I find out that
you're covering for him,

42:12.931 --> 42:16.301
I'll take everything
away from you.

42:16.334 --> 42:20.005
Your badge, your pension,

42:20.038 --> 42:23.208
and that's just for starters.

42:23.241 --> 42:26.845
Frank is not the one
you need to be scared of.

42:36.788 --> 42:39.557
[ Door opens, closes ]
